/td><td valign=top bgcolor=d1c3b5 class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usongmistressjenelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Songmistress Jenelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/01 9:40:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Since its Roleplaying prefered....</span><hr size=1> Welpers, you said it right in the title.  This server is roleplaying PREFERRED!  No, that does not mean that every second you log your character on you must roleplay or you will be banned.  But the EVIL ROLEPLAYING NAZIS!! will get you and scream your head off if you dare utter ONE question out of character.  However, roleplaying is appreciated.  I know that I joined this server because I looooove to play in character, and my sweet little bard is great to play out!  A lot of people joined this server especially because of this feature.  Verant did a lot to help with the roleplaying aspect of this server by increasing the realism.<br>
<br>
The roleplay tag, for instance, is a great idea.  You know, you don't walk around in real life with a little tag over your head that says your name.  People can't magically tell by typing a command into their little pocket computers what job you have, and how proficient you are.  No, silly, you have to TALK to people in real life.  Now I imagine this is what Verant is pushing people to do here.  We're supposed to roleplay.  Forgetting levels and dings, we're bards of the fifth song, clerics of the fifth prayer, fifth ranks, etc, etc!<br>
<br>
I agree with the absence of Out Of Character, but then again... I don't.  In an ideal world, out of character would only be used for OOC comments.  But you remember back when Everquest was young and everyone roleplayed anyway?  Well, that all stopped because of OOC run rampant.  Now, ooc conversations are bound to happen, but that's what the EVIL ROLEPLAYING GESTAPO is here for.  Sometimes I miss being able to OOC things.  But in reality (hello!), the OOC channel would become the most prominent.  Instead, auction and shout have been used primarily for what they SHOULD be used for.  It's customary to place (ooc) before any out of text comment, which is really helpful to filter through.  If we allowed an out of character channel, there would be too much discussion and not enough roleplaying.  And eventually, all the RPing would go down the drain :*(**.<br>
<br>
I sort of agree with the tells.. but only to an extent.  I think that tells are the best way to clarify OOC and IC.  I also think tells are a helpful way of &quot;whispering&quot; a comment to a groupmate.  Heck, you can consider tells practically shouts to someone.  It's just you're not disturbing the entire zone.<br>
<br>
I don't care about Human Language.. everyone should speak FAERIE, damnit!<br>
<br>
It's hard to roleplay, really, because this is an experience based game.  And let's face it, 99% of the population would rather be stickin' Lord Vyemm in the eye than courting some nekkid wood elf chick in GFay.  But, you know, while the server is young and the idea is fresh, let's enjoy the moment.  I hope to be roleplaying with you all until the spirit dies.<br>
<br>
Which it never will because as long as the Songmistress plays, the spirit lives on!<br>
